data.description:
UNDER CONTRACT BUT TAKING BACK-UPS!! Uncover Your Ideal Family Residence in the quaint Redfish Cove neighborhood with only 28 homes, this meticulously maintained two-story block home exudes undeniable charm. With four bedrooms, a versatile flex room, 2 1/2 bathrooms, and a generous 2320 square feet of living space, this dwelling is designed for families and those seeking a multi-generational sanctuary. As you step inside, the layout of this home will captivate you. Immersed with natural light, there is a warm and inviting atmosphere throughout. The expansive living areas offer ample space for both relaxation and entertainment, while the flex room allows for personalization to meet your lifestyle preferences. The heart of the home is the well-appointed kitchen, seamlessly combining style and functionality. Featuring abundant counter space, sleek white cabinetry, and high-end appliances, this kitchen is a delight for preparing family meals and hosting gatherings. Step outside to discover your private paradise, complete with lush avocado and mango trees, thriving banana and herb plants, and a backdrop of a tranquil conservation area, providing unparalleled serenity and privacy. Recent upgrades, such as freshly painted interiors, pressure-washed and stained pavers, and an epoxy-coated garage floor, showcase a commitment to home maintenance. Conveniently located in South Edgewater, you'll have access to a plethora of amenities, including reputable schools, shopping centers, and recreational facilities. Immerse yourself in the vibrant local community and explore numerous entertainment options just minutes away. This is a unique opportunity to transform this house into your family's forever home. Don't miss out - schedule your showing today and immerse yourself in the allure of this Floridian treasure.

Fun fact: This home falls with-in the USDA eligibility zone. What does that mean for you? That means that this home will qualify for 100% finanacing. Thats a savings of about $15,000. Imagine what you can do with that money.......Maybe buy your rate down??????
